It is successful to put the detection into practice, and it also needs to be fully verified that the detection is feasible in the sample extraction process to avoid concentration and spectral error. To ensure the accuracy of quantitative environmental monitoring, it shows the different concentration-intensity relationships of MG at the characteristic peak 1173 cm−1 (Fig. 6
                     ). The results show that the intensity of the signals of MG becomes stronger as the concentration increases (Fig. 6a). Notably, there is a good linear relationship for logarithmic fit of the peak intensity at 1173 cm−1 and the concentration of MG (log (C)) between 10−10 M and 10−4 M, and the R2 is 0.99154 close to 1 (Fig. 6b). This fitting relationship is perfectly suited as a basis for quantitative analysis in practical detection. Therefore, further spiked recoveries in river water and industrial wastewater are given for MG at 1, 100 and 10,000 nM extended to validate the potential of Ag-CDs-PBA substrate in complex environments. From the data analysis in Table 2
                     , it can be concluded that the MG recoveries in the two real samples were high between 94.10 % and 108.45 % and the calculated results were reliable and accurate (RSD was less than 5 %). The corresponding SERS spectra of MG in river water (Fig. 6c) and industrial wastewater (Fig. 6d) were represented and it was found that the intensity of the Raman spectra of the target molecule was slightly reduced in the detection of the actual water samples. Probably insoluble substances adsorbed near the nano-substrate merely have little effect on the performance in the counter-interference of the substrate and the characteristic bands of analyte can be identified clearly. In conclusion, Ag-CDs-PBA has a place in the practical applications of interference resistant structures for environmental monitoring. It is the rational design of this system that shows the multi-hot spot characteristics with strong SERS signals. It goes without saying that this Ag-CDs-PBA designed as a SERS substrate can be further applied to the commercial production with significant advantages and its bright future in the environmental and aquaculture industry.
